                <p class="lead">The unique multi-role design of the Atlas Endeavour isn’t the only thing that makes it stand out from the competition. The universal support of the Worlds Leading defence and technology manufacturers gives the Atlas Endeavour a unbeatable advantage.</p>
                <p>The mission statement of Hutchinson Defence is <em>“To provide engineered mobility solutions for all wheeled combat and off-road vehicles.”</em></p>
                <p>Hutchinson Defence, a subsidiary of Total, are able to draw on diverse research and chemical resources of one of the world’s largest petroleum and chemical manufacturers.</p>
                <p>Hutchinson Defence will be providing exclusive, full access to their state-of-the-art Vehicle Light Protection Kit VLPK.</p>
                <p>The vehicle is fitted with Hutchinson Hammerglass to ensure the highest possible standards of crew safety. It is heat resistant up to 650°c, is resistant to most chemicals and is available in ballistic protection classes from B4 (23mm) up to B6 (36mm). It removes the need for protective grids, thereby increasing crew visibility and vehicle manoeuvrability.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="col-sm-6">
                <p>The Hutchinson Defence Run-Flat Wheel System, which meets FINABEL A20A and 20A5 standards, ensures the mobility of the vehicle and the safety of the crew. It is approved for use at high speed (up to 50km/h) as well as on heavy load vehicles.</p>
                <p>The body of the Atlas Endeavour can be integrated with a highly ballistically resistant composite material. This is non-combustible and is designed to provide ballistic protection against hand grenades and handgun fires up to 7.62 x 39mm.</p>
                <p>The vehicle coating is a specialist Hutchinson Defence Polyurethane PU product. It can be applied in almost any colour and makes the vehicle non-combustible. It also works to isolate the crew compartment against extreme heat.</p>
                <p>Hutchinson Defence Safe Tank technology, which ensures fuel tanks don’t leak or catch fire under any circumstance can be specified when required.</p>
